INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2305495713, 'officer_tooltip_description_short_50300', '<color=#309BBF>Leader</color>
Provides Officer related buffs.

<color=#309BBF>Tactical</color>
Provides buffs against Hostiles.

<color=#309BBF>Explorer</color>
Provides buffs related to space exploration.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2305495713, 'officer_flavor_text_50300', 'A great man once said, “Don’t let them do anything that will take you off the bridge of that ship, because while you’re there, you can make a difference.”

Though he no longer commands the Enterprise, Admiral James Tiberius Kirk has never stopped making a difference.

Kirk’s tenure as a member of the Starfleet brass has been nothing short of historic. From stopping the homicidal Augment leader, Khan Noonien Singh, to navigating a murky peace process with the Klingons, this legendary figure in Starfleet has continued to sow the seeds of history wherever he walks.

Despite all these achievements, however, Kirk still feels the call of the captain’s chair. He longs to break away from the summits, the delegations, and the hearings. He longs to step foot on a starship again, to explore strange new worlds, to seek out new life and new civilizations... Just like the old days.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2305495713, 'officer_name_50300', 'Admiral Kirk', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2305495713, 'officer_name_short_50300', 'Admiral Kirk', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2305495713, 'officer_name_short_50300', 'KIRK', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (284701693, 'officer_tooltip_description_short_50301', '<color=#309BBF>Miner</color>
Provides Mining related buffs.

<color=#309BBF>Architect</color>
Provides Station related buffs.

<color=#309BBF>Scientist</color>
Provides Research and other fascinating buffs.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (284701693, 'officer_flavor_text_50301', 'Some men, they say, are destined for greatness.

Spock’s unprecedented career would only continue to grow after the Enterprise’s five-year mission came to an end. He returned to Vulcan to undergo the Kolinahr ritual, in order to purge himself of all emotion. 

However, he would be forced to abandon the ritual in order to, once again, join the Enterprise on a mission of galactic peace. He, along with the rest of the crew, solved the V’ger crisis, and Spock was once more shown the power that empathy and friendship can hold. 
Choosing not to forsake emotions, Spock instead returned to Starfleet Academy, where he was promoted to Captain. There, he spends his days training cadets, ensuring that the future of Starfleet remains bright.

They say some men are destined for greatness. If you asked Spock, he would tell you that he was simply in the right place at the right time. Any other suppositions are merely... illogical.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (284701693, 'officer_name_50301', 'Captain Spock', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (284701693, 'officer_name_short_50301', 'SPOCK', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2807368027, 'officer_tooltip_description_short_50302', '<color=#309BBF>Combatant</color>
Provides buffs against Players.

<color=#309BBF>Admiral</color>
Provides buffs against Armadas.

<color=#309BBF>Mechanic</color>
Provides Ship related buffs.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2807368027, 'officer_flavor_text_50302', '“They took everything I was. They used me to kill and to destroy... and I couldn’t stop them.”

There is nothing so tragic as a good man forced to commit acts of evil.

Jean-Luc Picard is a man of principle, devotion, and morality. He dedicated his life to the pursuit of human advancement and peaceful coexistence. 

All of that was swept away under the influence of the Borg. 

No longer in control of his own mind or body, the person known as Jean-Luc was pushed to the background, forced to watch as he committed unspeakable atrocities under a new name... Locutus of Borg. 

He witnessed his strategic acumen used against his own people at Wolf 359. Were it not for the bravery of the Enterprise crew, he may have been weaponized against Earth itself.

One thing is certain, no new technology, no devastating weapon, no galaxy spanning armada will ever be as threatening, as utterly terrifying, as a good man turned to evil.', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2807368027, 'officer_name_50302', 'Locutus of Borg', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
INSERT INTO officer_translations (officer_id, key, text, modified) VALUES (2807368027, 'officer_name_short_50302', 'LOCUTUS', '2025-08-13 17:11:38');
